<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-133-650  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 133 650.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Publish!andP;  April 1989 v4 n4 p86(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Special-effects smorgasbord: Cricket Paint. (Software Review)(paint program) (evaluation)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Wigham, Laurie.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Cricket Software's $195 black-and-white paint-only program for theMacintosh, Cricket Paint 1.0, is recommended as a worthwhilepurchase for its special effects.andP;  The program prints onlybit-mapped art with jagged edges, and users can not combinehigh-resolution drawn objects with painted bit maps in the samedocument.andP;  Cricket Paint's key feature is Freshpaint, which allowsusers to draw an object with 'wet paint' that can be easilymodified, but there are some limitations when using special tools.andO;The program also has some innovative texture effects, such as theability to create a 'linen' look in clothing.andP;  Keyboard commandsare plentiful, and the program is easy to use and learn, but itlacks a dialog box for reducing and enlarging at specifiedpercentages.andP;  Cricket Paint requires 1Mbyte of RAM, two floppydrives and is recommended for use on a system 6.0.2.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Cricket Software (products).andO;Product:   Apple Macintosh (Microcomputer) (computer programs)Cricket Paint (Computer graphics software).andO;Topic:     EvaluationGraphics Software.andO;Feature:   illustrationtablephotograph.andO;Caption:   Product information. (table)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>